race.comment: PARKRUN (2) lines up for the new stable and looks an each-way chance. It's hard to line up his NSW form but he shown glimpses of ability that suggest he can run well here. Like a few in this race, the recent form of SPOT THE GREY (4) is patchy but his best is good enough and he is well placed here to sneak into the minor money. SO REGAL (12) was better last time and can keep improving. Hard fit and could be ready to show what he can do. DODGY ELEMENT (1) might be another that can run a cheeky race at a price. DISCOBAY (7) is resuming from a break and will be fitter for a recent jump-out at Cranbourne. Can feature fresh.
